<item>
            <title>[SPR-2866] &lt;form:password&gt; tag returns password to web browser if form returned with errors</title>
                <link>https://jira.spring.io/browse/SPR-2866</link>
                <project id="10000" key="SPR">Spring Framework</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;When using the &amp;lt;form:password&amp;gt; tag, if the page is returned for correction of input, the submitted password is also returned which is a security vulnerability since it is then embedded in the HTML. This tag should never render any value at all!&lt;/p&gt;</description>
            <key id="15541">SPR-2866</key>
            <summary>&lt;form:password&gt; tag returns password to web browser if form returned with errors</summary>
                <type id="1" iconUrl="https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/issuetypes/bug.png">Bug</type>
                                            <priority id="3" iconUrl="https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/priorities/major.png">Major</priority>
                        <status id="6" iconUrl="https://jira.spring.io/images/icons/statuses/closed.png" description="The issue is considered finished, the resolution is correct. Issues which are not closed can be reopened.">Closed</status>
                    <statusCategory id="3" key="done" colorName="green"/>
